#define ANIMESH_STRENGTH 100000
#define STAND "Explosive animation - Stretch"
#define LAND "Explosive animation - Male Crouch Pose 2"
#define WALK "Explosive animation - Walk 11 Power Walk"

#define GREETINGS ["Try not to break a bone bowing, mortal. My metallic footsteps alone possess more force than your entire frail lineage.","Careful where you stand, fragile one. A mere sigh from my bronze lungs might snap your spine.","Are you made of paper? Stay back; I'd hate to accidentally crush you before I've even introduced myself.","Hephaestus wouldn't even use you as kindling for his forge. Scurry away before you get stepped on.","I have joints that require more torque to move than your entire body can generate. Flee before you get hurt.","You lift weights? How quaint. I lift mountains without scratching my polish.","I see you've trained your little flesh-muscles. Adorable. Now behold true, unyielding divine metallurgy.","A decent specimen of meat and bone, I suppose. It will make the sound of your crushing all the more satisfying.","You might impress your fellow mortals, but to a titan of bronze and fire, you are nothing but dust.","Strike me with all your might. Let me enjoy the sound of your knuckles shattering against my hull.","The absolute pinnacle of human biology... and yet, still softer than the cheapest tin in my maker's scrap pile.","You push the limits of flesh, mortal. Let me show you what happens when flesh meets invincible Olympian steel.","A masterpiece of genetics! It's a shame I'm a masterpiece of the gods. You don't stand a chance.","You've trained your whole life just to reach the baseline of my left pinky finger. Welcome to your ceiling.","Impressive for a blood-bag. Too bad for you, perfection was forged in a volcano, not a gymnasium.","Ah, you can toss a chariot or a mortal vehicle! Good for you. I was forged to juggle continents.","You hit harder than the average pest, but against god-forged armor, you're just ringing the dinner bell.","So you have a little power in those veins. Unfortunately, my hydraulics are fueled by the absolute might of Olympus.","A cute display of strength. Need help lifting that? No? Good, because I'm just here to drop it on you.","You punch hard enough to dent iron. A pity for you that Hephaestus uses materials far beyond your comprehension.","Finally, someone who won't immediately explode when I backhand them. Do try to entertain me for more than a second.","You can lift a tank! Bravo. I use them as target practice. Let’s see if you dent before you break.","You have strength that mortals fear, yet you still look upon a walking god of metal. Bow, or be broken.","Don't mistake that parlor-trick strength of yours for a threat. I am invincible; you are merely heavy-lifting.","I'll give you the first strike. Give it everything you have—I want to see the despair in your eyes when I don't even flinch.","A true heavy hitter! But rocks, flesh, and earthly metals all crumble the same under the weight of divine engineering.","You think your brute force makes you a titan? I was forged by the lord of fire to be the immovable object and the unstoppable force.","Shake the earth all you want. I was born in the heart of a volcano, and your tantrums do not impress me.","You're used to being the strongest one in the room, aren't you? It's a shame we just stepped into my arena.","Come, let us clash! We'll see how long that famous stamina lasts when you're striking impenetrable Olympian steel.","They call your strength limitless. Let's put that myth to the test against the absolute perfection of Hephaestus's ultimate creation.","Even gods fall before me, so don't expect your 'incalculable' power to leave a single scratch on this finish.","World-breakers? Galaxy-shakers? All just loud words until they meet the flawless, unbreakable metal of my fists.","You may move planets, but you cannot move me. I am the apex of strength, and today, you learn your limits.","Go ahead. Unleash your rage, your magic, your endless power. It will only make my inevitable victory that much more glorious."]

#define WrestleWin ["I've locked your limbs, mortal. Try not to snap your own brittle bone constraints just by squirming.","Is this resistance, or are you just shivering? My structural integrity isn't even registering your struggle.","I could maintain this hold for a millennium without a fraction of mechanical fatigue. You, however, are already turning blue.","Careful now. A single twitch of my hydraulics and your fragile framework will permanently shatter.","I barely applied any torque and you are completely immobilized. How do you even survive the gravity of this planet?","A standard biological specimen, neatly folded into a perfect lock. Your muscle fatigue is already a mathematical certainty.","Did you really think your daily physical routines prepared you to break a hold forged by Hephaestus?","I've calculated your exact escape window. It's zero. Enjoy your time on the mat.","Squirm all you want. Your basic strength gains are entirely insufficient to overcome even my lightest grip.","You leverage your flesh; I leverage divine mechanics. The outcome of this grapple was decided before we touched.","The absolute peak of human capability, completely neutralized by a simple arm-bar. How embarrassing for your species.","I can feel your lactic acid peaking as you desperately try to break my grip. It's futile, meat-sack.","Perfect biological technique won't save you when I have an absolute advantage in structural integrity.","You trained your whole life to be the strongest mortal, just to be easily pinned by a bronze god who isn't even trying.","Your strength maxes out right where my idle resting state begins. Yield, before your tendons snap.","Oh, are you pushing back? How cute. My secondary servos haven't even engaged to keep you pinned.","You may toss vehicles around, but locked in my grasp, you're just another biological system experiencing catastrophic failure.","I modeled this exact hold in my combat matrix. Your superhuman muscles are already approaching maximum fatigue.","You have power, yes, but against divine metallurgy, your leverage is completely nullified.","Go ahead, try to muscle out of it! I want to hear the exact moment your enhanced ligaments realize they cannot bend bronze.","You hit like a siege engine, but trapped in this grapple, your kinetic output drops to absolute zero.","A valiant struggle! Your force output is impressive, but my chassis was forged to contain the fury of volcanoes.","You're burning through your energy reserves trying to break this lock. My mechanics, however, are inexhaustible.","You think sheer strength can break my hold? My mathematical models of your failure are proving highly accurate right now.","I have you completely immobilized. All that heavy lifting, and you're still just thrashing in the dirt like an insect.","They call you a behemoth, yet here you are, folded and helpless under the weight of true Olympian perfection.","Push with all your might! It only makes the sound of your structural integrity failing that much sweeter.","You've never been pinned like this, have you? Get used to it. The unstoppable force just met the unbreakable lock.","I calculate your frustration is growing exponentially as your colossal strength gains amount to absolutely nothing.","To the mortals, you are a titan. To me, you're just another rigid object waiting to be bent out of shape.","Limitless strength? We'll see about that. Right now, your 'incalculable' power can't even break my wrist lock.","Scream, rage, shake the earth—it doesn't matter. You cannot break the grip of a god-forged machine.","I've locked down your inverse kinematics so completely that all your infinite power has nowhere to go but back into your own useless struggles.","The universe fears your might, but under my heel, you are mathematically proven to be inferior.","You are an engine of destruction, but I am the ultimate cage. Enjoy your eternity trapped in this hold."]

#define WrestleDefeat ["A lucky slip of my gears! Your frail biomechanics couldn't possibly compromise my structural integrity on purpose.","Enjoy this momentary leverage, mortal. I merely let you secure that grip so you wouldn't snap your own brittle joints trying to catch me.","Did you grease your skin? There is zero mathematical probability a creature incapable of lifting its own body weight outmaneuvered me without a trick.","Fascinating. Your utter lack of muscle density actually allowed you to slip through my grasp. Don't mistake flexibility for a strength gain.","Hold on as tight as you like, insect. Since you lack the kinetic output to actually cause fatigue to my chassis, I'll just wait until you tire yourself out.","You found a decent fulcrum point, I'll admit. But basic leverage won't save you when I actually engage my primary hydraulics.","A textbook hold for a standard human. Let's see how well your flesh holds up when I simply stand up.","You think pinning my arm means something? I don't experience muscle fatigue, meat-sack. You're just delaying the inevitable.","Clever footwork. You utilized my own momentum against me. Enjoy the view from my back before I crush you.","Congratulations, you have an average mortal's grip strength. Now watch what happens when I apply divine torque.","Incredible technique for a biological organism, but technique merely compensates for your inherent weakness.","You pushed your physical limits to secure this lock. Too bad my bronze joints have an infinite threshold for stress.","A perfect suplex form! I can appreciate the kinetic output, but my internal structure wasn't even dented.","You've maxed out your flesh's potential to trap me here. Let's see if your tendons snap before my patience does.","Impressive grip metrics. But while your lactic acid builds and biological fatigue sets in, my power remains absolute.","Alright, so you have enough raw force to bend my wrist. That just means I get to stop holding back.","You bypassed my center of gravity with surprising output. Consider it a minor miscalculation in my defensive algorithms.","An impressive lock! You're stressing my secondary servos, but you're a long way from compromising my main chassis.","I felt that impact. Good structural alignment on your part, but let's see you maintain this hold when the forge-fire inside me vents.","You managed to ground me with enhanced mass and leverage. Consider it the absolute peak of your wrestling career.","You actually possess the torque to restrict my movement. Fascinating. Now, let me show you what true god-metal can endure.","A solid grapple. My pressure sensors are actually registering your effort. Let's test who exhausts their energy reserves first.","You wrestled me to the dirt! I applaud your physical output, but dirt is where mortals belong. I belong in the heavens.","You think this hold means victory? You've only trapped yourself in my immediate strike zone with nowhere to run.","I allowed you to close the distance so I could measure your strength gains. You're strong, but you're not Hephaestus-strong.","You actually have the sheer kinetic power to force me to a knee. I didn't think terrestrial muscle could achieve such structural integrity.","A crushing grip! Any lesser construct would have shattered. It's a privilege for you to wrestle something that won't immediately turn to paste.","To overpower my hydraulic baseline takes titanic force. But an immovable object doesn't care if it's placed in a headlock.","You matched my force output and found the perfect leverage. But while you sweat and strain, I am just getting warmed up.","So, you can grapple a walking mountain. Try not to break your back maintaining this position.","Impossible. Your sheer physical mass output is defying every law of divine mechanics I was programmed with!","You shattered my stance and broke my grip! But holding down divine perfection requires more than just incalculable brute force.","My chassis is groaning under your hold. I didn't know organic fibers could generate such terrifying leverage without tearing themselves apart!","You've pinned the un-pinnable. But mechanical fatigue does not exist for me, and I will be waiting when your grip eventually falters.","A flawless display of infinite strength and tactical mechanics. But ask yourself this: now that you've caught the god of metal, what exactly do you plan to do with him?"]
